ex microservices architecture you designed.\\n     2. How does AWS ECS compare to Kubernetes (EKS)? When would you choose one over the other?\\n     3. You need to optimize a slow API endpoint. Outline your step-by-step approach.\\n     4. Compare PostgreSQL, MongoDB, and Redis for a high-throughput system. Use cases and trade-offs.\\n     5. How do you approach writing unit tests and practicing TDD?\\n     6. Describe a complex production issue you debugged. What tools/processes did you use?\\n     7. Explain RESTful API design best practices, including versioning and documentation.\\n   Follow-up:\\n     • How would you handle breaking changes in an existing API without disrupting clients?\\n\\n4. Send emails as and when needed:\\n   - Sent interview invitation email to Jane Doe one week in advance.\\n   - Confirmed interview schedule and call link 24 hours prior.\\n   - Sent thank-you/follow-up email within 2 hours post-interview.\\n   - Notified stakeholders with interim scoring the same day.\\n\\n5. Score candidate responses:\\n   - Used a 10-point scale per question; follow-up scored out of 5.\\n   - Scoring rubric focused on correctness, depth, clarity, and practical experience.\\n\\n6. Generate final evaluation report:\\n   - Combined job requirements, resume summary, detailed scored responses.\\n   - Calculated overall score out of 100.\\n   - Provided actionable recommendation and interviewer notes.\\n\\n========================\\nFinal Evaluation Report\\n========================\\n\\nCandidate Name: Jane Doe\\nRole Interviewed For: Interviewer/Assessor\\nDate: 2024-06-15\\n\\n1. Microservices Architecture\\nQuestion: Describe a complex microservices architecture you designed.\\nResponse Summary:\\n  • Designed 12-service ecosystem for e-commerce platform.\\n  • Used Spring Boot services behind API Gateway (AWS API Gateway).\\n  • Employed event-driven communication via Kafka.\\n  • Deployed on AWS ECS with auto-scaling, Blue/Green deployments.\\nScore: 9