ion Debugging\\nQuestion: Describe a production issue you debugged. Tools/processes?\\nResponse Summary:\\n  • Memory leak in microservice causing OOM.\\n  • Used AWS X-Ray for tracing, Heap dumps, and Eclipse MAT.\\n  • Rolled back faulty deployment, patched GC settings, added heap monitoring.\\nScore: 9/10\\nRationale: Good diagnostic workflow; could mention alerts configuration.\\nRed Flags: None.\\n\\n7. RESTful API Best Practices\\nQuestion: Explain RESTful API design best practices, including versioning and documentation.\\nResponse Summary:\\n  • Use resource-oriented URIs, proper HTTP verbs.\\n  • Versioning via URI (/v1/) or header.\\n  • Document with OpenAPI/Swagger; auto-generate client SDKs.\\nScore: 9/10\\nRationale: Covers core principles; could discuss HATEOAS.\\nRed Flags: None.\\n\\nFollow-up Question\\nQuestion: How would you handle breaking changes in an existing API without disrupting clients?\\nResponse Summary:\\n  • Introduce new version parallelly.\\n  • Deprecate old endpoints with clear notices and sunset timeline.\\n  • Maintain backward compatibility for 3 months.\\nScore: 5/5\\nRationale: Prudent versioning strategy and communication.\\nRed Flags: None.\\n\\nOverall Score Calculation:\\n  Total points earned: 9+8+10+9+8+9+9 = 62/70\\n  Follow-up: 5/5\\n  Aggregate: 67/75 = 89%\\n  Scaled to 100: 89/100\\n\\nOverall Recommendation: Strong Hire\\n\\nInterviewer Notes:\\n  - Jane demonstrates deep architectural experience and clear problem-solving steps.\\n  - Communicates technical concepts effectively.\\n  - Minor gaps in edge-case considerations but easily trainable.\\n  - Excellent fit for the Interviewer/Assessor role and company culture.\\n\\n========================\\nEnd of .txt File\\n========================\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\n\\nYour task is to take interview. The following are the steps\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the can