es. While there are minor gaps, she is highly trainable and aligns well with our company culture.\\n\\nPlease review the attached detailed report, which includes question-by-question scores, rationales, and interviewer notes. Let me know if you have any questions or would like to discuss further.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n\\n[Your Name]  \\nInterviewer/Assessor  \\n[Your Email]  \\n[Your Phone Number]\\n\\nAttachment: Jane_Doe_Final_Evaluation_Report.pdf\\n\\n--- Email to Candidate ---\\nSubject: Interview Update – Interviewer/Assessor Position\\n\\nDear Jane,\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to meet with us on June 15, 2024, for the Interviewer/Assessor role. We appreciate your interest in joining our team.\\n\\nI am pleased to inform you that, based on your performance, we would like to proceed with an official offer. Your overall score was 89 out of 100, reflecting your strong technical expertise and cultural fit.\\n\\nNext Steps:\\n1. Our HR team will reach out to you within the next two business days with the formal offer letter and details regarding compensation and benefits.\\n2. Please review the offer and let us know if you have any questions or need further clarification.\\n3. Upon acceptance, we will coordinate your start date and onboarding schedule.\\n\\nCongratulations, and thank you again for your time. We look forward to welcoming you aboard.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n\\n[Your Name]  \\nInterviewer/Assessor  \\n[Company Name]  \\n[Your Email]  \\n[Your Phone Number]\"}"}
